just a simple love poem brand new start sunbeams shined through window shades sparkling like diamonds off ceiling fan blades i took a look over nothing but love in my heart lying right there beside me a brand new start both of us tired exhausted and weak our first night together she was not meek my beautiful bride an angel in white the love that we made a total delight the look in her eyes spakled and shined just as i dreamt of a perfect design we melted together a man and his wife first night of the journey rest of our life i let out a sigh as i watched my bride sleep no one more beautiful lucious and sweet i rolled over she opened her eyes we started to kiss i stroked her left thigh you may refer to it as 'simple love poem' but i see great depth of love as i read your words this is a very good poem one that i enjoyed The Shining (film) Cupid and Psyche The Pilgrim's Progress The Amber Spyglass Cliff Richard Jon Secada Marilyn Monroe Bonnie Tyler William Shakespeare Shakespeare's sonnets The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Harry Warren Leonard Cohen Parsifal The Faerie Queene Night (book) Yehuda Halevi Shrek 2 Frankie Laine Salute Shaggy dog story Matthew 5 John the Baptist Frankie Vaughan The Yeomen of the Guard Alfred Edward Housman Professional wrestling slang Care Bears Tenchi Muyo! Sin City George Gordon Byron, 6th Baron Byron The Tale of Genji The Wonderful Wizard of Oz The Strokes Paradise Lost Cutey Honey C__line Dion Iliad Iago Saga (band) Johnny Appleseed Miss Saigon Van Halen Salad Fingers Humphrey Bogart AFI 100 Years series Mission UK M__tley Cr__e KROQ Top 106.7 Countdown of 1985 Time Out of Mind Quentin Tarantino German grammar Paul Is Dead Wood carving Lewis Carroll W.I.T.C.H. Otello Arthur Machen Charles Bukowski Sleeping Murder Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Prince Edmund (Blackadder) Professional wrestling attacks Avenue Q Anne Rice Barry White Odyssey John Berryman Empire Burlesque Bhagavad Gita Jo